  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "Here are a few ways to check if someone has deleted you on LINE:\n\n1. Check their profile\n- If they've deleted you, you won't be able to see their profile picture or status\n- Their name might appear differently or as a phone number\n\n2. Message status\n- If your previous messages show only one checkmark instead of two, it could indicate you've been deleted\n- If messages don't show \"Read\" status anymore\n\n3. Contact list\n- Check if they're still in your contact list\n- If they've disappeared, they might have deleted you\n\n4. Try to send a message\n- If you can't send a message or it doesn't go through, you might have been deleted\n\n5. Search their ID\n- Try searching for their LINE ID\n- If you can't find them, they may have blocked or deleted you\n\n6. Mutual friends\n- Ask a mutual friend if they can still see the person's profile\n\nNote: These are not definitive proof, and LINE doesn't provide an official \"deleted\" notification. The most reliable method is direct communication or checking multiple signs together.",
